Obálendé, nke ndị Yoruba na-akpọkwa Ibi ti Oba le wa de, nke pụtara "Ebe eze chụgara anyị", bụ agbata obi Lagos, Nigeria, nke dị na Eti-Osa LGA, nso Lagos Island. Gọọmentị steeti Lagos kewara Eti-Osa n'ime mpaghara mmepe obodo (LCDA) nke Ikoyi Obalende bụ otu n'ime ha
O nwere ọtụtụ ụlọ akwụkwọ, gụnyere Holy Child College Obalende, St Gregory's College, Aunty Ayo International School na Girls Secondary Grammar School
Ọ dị n'akụkụ ụlọ ndị uwe ojii na ụlọ ndị agha
Obalende jupụtara na mmadụ ma jupụta na ya
Obalende bụ nke a ma ama maka ndụ abalị ya, mpaghara ọkụ ya na-acha ọbara ọbara na maka suya ya na njikọ a na-akpọkarị njikọ Suya.
Ndị Royal West African Frontier Force (RWAFF) nke ndị ikom Hausa mejupụtara na mbụ mara ụlọikwuu n'ala ebe King's College, Lagos dị
Mgbe ahụ, mkpa bilitere maka iji ala ahụ mee ihe na Oba nke Lagos manyere Gọvanọ nke Lagos ka ọ weghachite ndị RWAFF, ma ree ala na-amaghị nwoke n'ihe bụ Obalende ugbu a na Gọọmentị British Colonial
Mgbe ha kwagara n'ala ahụ ha zụrụ, ndị RWAFF kpọrọ ebe ahụ Ibi ti Ọba lé wà dé, nke a pụtara "ebe eze chugara anyị".
